result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley S Jamerson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Ashley S Jamerson in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court vacates the stayed bench warrant.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, Defense and Defendant.   Court orders defendant pay a fine in the amount of $250.00 INCLUDING Court costs and all applicable surcharges and assessments.  Find due by July 5, 2016; nonpayment penalty shall result in a civil judgment.

Defendant Ashley S Jamerson in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Jaclyn Schwartz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
Case set for sentencing. Defendant could not get off of work.  Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed the issuance until next court date.  Court ordered case adjourned for calendar call and sentencing on 1/05/16 at 1:30 in Branch 40.  All parties were informed that as of December 14, 2015, this case will be assigned to Judge Janet Protasiewicz, Branch 24 in Room 501 of the Courthouse.  Calendar call scheduled for January 5, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

AS TO COUNT 1:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 40.

Defendant Ashley S Jamerson in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Jaclyn Schwartz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.  
On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to Disorderly Conduct, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 947.01(1), a Class B Misdemeanor.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for November 30, 2015 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Ashley S Jamerson in court with attorney Ramon Arellano Valdez.  Matthew James Torbenson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: rmm.
Case set for jury trial.  Parties are ready to proceed.  Court is in trial and another court could not be found to hear this case.    Court ordered case adjourned for jury trial in Branch 40.  Court advised defendant that the no contact order remains in effect.  Jury trial scheduled for November 2, 2015 at 08:30 am.
